[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 5.31,
        "duration": 1.462
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 6.772,
        "duration": 3.333
    },
    {
        "text": "First, rinse the salted wakame seaweed ",
        "start": 18.046,
        "duration": 3.297
    },
    {
        "text": "in a large bowl or under running water.",
        "start": 21.343,
        "duration": 3.939
    },
    {
        "text": "Squeeze ",
        "start": 28.197,
        "duration": 1.082
    },
    {
        "text": "and place the wakame into another bowl of water.",
        "start": 29.279,
        "duration": 4.038
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, squeeze the wakame ",
        "start": 44.707,
        "duration": 3.017
    },
    {
        "text": "and blanch it in a pot of boiling water.",
        "start": 48.384,
        "duration": 3.583
    },
    {
        "text": "Remove and pour cold water over it.",
        "start": 54.218,
        "duration": 4.181
    },
    {
        "text": "Squeeze out the excess water.",
        "start": 59.538,
        "duration": 2.984
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, cut the wakame seaweed into bite-size pieces.",
        "start": 63.776,
        "duration": 5.347
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let’s make the dressing.",
        "start": 70.391,
        "duration": 2.935
    },
    {
        "text": "Combine the soy sauce, ",
        "start": 73.326,
        "duration": 1.434
    },
    {
        "text": "vinegar, ",
        "start": 74.76,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "dashi stock ",
        "start": 78.042,
        "duration": 1.835
    },
    {
        "text": "and the sugar.",
        "start": 81.477,
        "duration": 1.683
    },
    {
        "text": "Dissolve it thoroughly.",
        "start": 83.782,
        "duration": 2.135
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, add the olive oil ",
        "start": 85.917,
        "duration": 2.817
    },
    {
        "text": "and grated ginger root.",
        "start": 90.027,
        "duration": 3.009
    },
    {
        "text": "Mix the dressing thoroughly.",
        "start": 93.192,
        "duration": 2.879
    },
    {
        "text": "And now, cut the mizuna greens into 5cm or 2 inch pieces.",
        "start": 98.735,
        "duration": 6.817
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the greens into a bowl.",
        "start": 107.549,
        "duration": 2.804
    },
    {
        "text": "Cut the cherry tomatoes in half.",
        "start": 112.453,
        "duration": 3.251
    },
    {
        "text": "Shred the daikon radish with a slicer.",
        "start": 120.153,
        "duration": 3.373
    },
    {
        "text": "Likewise, shred the carrot.",
        "start": 127.161,
        "duration": 3.006
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the daikon and carrot to the bowl.",
        "start": 133.797,
        "duration": 3.518
    },
    {
        "text": "With kitchen chopsticks, mix it evenly.",
        "start": 138.1,
        "duration": 5.501
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, place the vegetables into a bowl.",
        "start": 146.086,
        "duration": 3.786
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the wakame seaweed on top.",
        "start": 151.378,
        "duration": 3.479
    },
    {
        "text": "Garnish with a bit of the vegetables.",
        "start": 156.092,
        "duration": 3.549
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, lightly grind the toasted sesame seeds.",
        "start": 161.691,
        "duration": 4.668
    },
    {
        "text": "Sprinkle the sesame on the salad.",
        "start": 170.195,
        "duration": 3.182
    },
    {
        "text": "Garnish with the tomato ",
        "start": 175.67,
        "duration": 2.236
    },
    {
        "text": "and the kaiware radish sprouts or garden cress.",
        "start": 180.69,
        "duration": 4.292
    },
    {
        "text": "Finally, mix the dressing again ",
        "start": 185.414,
        "duration": 3.194
    },
    {
        "text": "and then pour it over the wakame salad.",
        "start": 189.561,
        "duration": 3.828
    },
    {
        "text": "You can use your favorite raw vegetables. ",
        "start": 196.552,
        "duration": 3.433
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, lettuce leaves, baby salad greens, ",
        "start": 199.985,
        "duration": 4.503
    },
    {
        "text": "cucumber or sprouts are great.",
        "start": 204.488,
        "duration": 2.987
    },
    {
        "text": "The dried seaweed mix, cut wakame ",
        "start": 207.927,
        "duration": 3.347
    },
    {
        "text": "or kanten can be also used.",
        "start": 211.274,
        "duration": 2.499
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also add a small portion of grated garlic ",
        "start": 225.381,
        "duration": 3.733
    },
    {
        "text": "to the dressing to taste.",
        "start": 229.114,
        "duration": 2.337
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen.",
        "start": 231.451,
        "duration": 1.734
    }
]